snippet.textDisplay:
Flour doesn't look like a raw food, but typically it is. This means it hasn't been treated to kill germs such as Escherichia coli (E. coli), which causes food poisoning (foodborne illness). ... This is why you should never taste or eat raw dough or batter—whether made from recalled flour or any other flour.
--- The CDC

snippet.textDisplay: That cookie dough is technically not safe to eat, raw flour can still contain contaminants that can get you very very sick. If you want to make completely safe to eat raw cookie dough you need to use pasteurized flour. You can make this yourself by placing your flour in a microwave safe bowl and nuking for about a minute. Then using a candy thermometer, temp the center of the flour in the bowl, if it hits at least 160F you are good to go! Another tip for raw cookie dough is using pasteurized eggs as well, such as egg beaters. But either way you do it, aquafaba or eggs, just make sure you're being safe! No need to get yourself sick for no reason, especially right now, lol.
